      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2103: 🔴 Critical Issues - The retry state is never reset when a new registration/connectivity cycle starts after all retries are exhausted. Once `state.exhausted` becomes true, future identity announcement failures return immediately forever, so a transient outage can permanently disable the intended recovery until some unrelated success path resets the state. Reset the retry state when the account reconnects/registers or when scheduling a new identity announcement cycle, rather than keeping an exhausted state across cycles.\n\n```suggestion\n// Reset identity announcement retry state when starting a new registration cycle.\nif (identityRetryState_) {\n    identityRetryState_-\u003etimer.cancel();\n    identityRetryState_.reset();\n}\n```\nPlace this at the start of the registration/DHT startup path that precedes a fresh identity announcement, or otherwise key the retry state to an explicit registration generation.",
