      "message": "[Medium] Line 2707: 🟡 Suggestions - `connectivityChanged()` now refreshes presence on every connectivity notification while the DHT is running, even if connectivity did not actually transition from disconnected to connected. Depending on how often this callback fires, this can repeatedly clear and recreate all buddy listeners, causing unnecessary DHT churn for accounts with many contacts. Consider gating this on an actual reconnection/registration transition, or debouncing the refresh through the account event loop.\n\n```suggestion\nif (presenceManager_ \u0026\u0026 dht_ \u0026\u0026 dht_-\u003eisRunning() \u0026\u0026 wasDisconnected)\n    presenceManager_-\u003erefresh();\n```\nUse the existing account/connectivity state if available rather than refreshing unconditionally.",
